## What This Teaching Does

Appends a high-impact signal to `WAI-Spoke/lugs/bytype/signal/undelivered/` on this spoke.

## Embedded Signal

```json
{
  "id": "signal-settings-json-env-var-hook-failure-v1",
  "type": "signal",
  "status": "undelivered",
  "title": "settings.json hook commands with $CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR silently fail — use absolute paths",
  "impact": 9,
  "signal": "Claude Code does not expand environment variables in settings.json hook command strings. A command like '$CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR/.claude/hooks/pre-tool-guard.sh' is passed literally to the OS — the dollar-sign path is never resolved, causing the hook to silently error on every invocation. This was the root cause of Minder's PreToolUse hook errors. Inside hook .sh scripts, $CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR works fine (CC sets it as env var). Only the settings.json 'command' value is affected. Fix: use absolute paths. The hook-compliance-full-stack-v1 teaching was deploying this broken pattern to all spokes — now fixed.",
  "rationale": "Every spoke that adopted the hook-compliance teaching has this broken settings.json. verify_teaching_installed() now checks for $CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR and flags for reinstall. Tonight's Tender run will fix all affected spokes retroactively.",
  "routed_to": "SIGNAL",
  "scope": "all_spokes",
